N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 8 ยง 166.2 - Definitions

State Regulations

For purposes of this Part: (a) Approved not-for-profit educational
agency means a school district, board of cooperative educational services, postsecondary institution, community-based organization or private school that
operates on a not-for-profit basis and has been approved by the commissioner as
a provider of adult basic education. (b) Eligible agency means labor
organizations, their federations or organizations of employers acting in
consortium with labor organizations, that have been approved by the
commissioner, upon application therefor, to conduct workplace literacy and
basic skills education programs. Notes
